<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>The club came up with a plan of action to raise funds by presenting a 10km club run around Katlehong in Ekurhuleni.It’s part of their community upliftment programme that collects sanitary pads to donate to needy pupils.Just this past weekend the club collected a whopping 300 sanitary packs which they will distribute at three schools they have identified so far.Club member Hloni Motloung said it was all about instilling dignity in the girls.“These products will be donated to local schools in the community to ensure we keep a girl child in school and instil a sense of dignity and pride. “Our intention is to ensure each girl child can go to the staff room to get sanitary pads at school so she can continue with her lessons and not miss school.” The club urged the community to support their initiative so that more pupils are helped.“The initiative is aimed at empowering the community and empowering young people in these tough economic times we face as a country.“We will continue to spread the word through running to reach more girls,” said Hloni